{
  "texts": [
    "Rich resources targeting key agronomic traits didn't support complex analysis involved in precise crop breeding 3, 19, 20, such as plant metaphenomics database 21, Plant Trait database TRY 22, and plant image analysis database 23.",
    "Several genome databases, such as TropGeneDB 24, AtMAD 25, PGP 26, SesameFG 27, GWAS Atlas 28, and MaizeGDB 29, have integrated and utilized genomic, genetic, and phenotypic data.",
    "However, these databases have not considered all the necessary factors for crop breeding.",
    "The progress commonly relies on manual labeling for data population and updating, which can be costly and time-consuming.",
    "However, advancements in artificial intelligence brought an unparalleled opportunity to mine big biological data."
  ]
}